{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GueLSMW6cczFRCXbWjkJcQ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my thorough search of the codebase, here's a comprehensive report of all URL routing for runs endpoints:\n\n## Summary of Runs Endpoint Routing\n\n### Route Definitions (in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - lines 139-162)\n\nThe main handler registers the following runs-related routes:\n\n**HTML Routes (Server-rendered pages):**\n- `GET /` - Project overview page\n- `GET /runs` - List all runs across all projects (handles legacy `?project=` redirects)\n- `GET /runs/{id}` - Run detail page for a specific run\n- `GET /projects/{name}` - Project detail page\n- `GET /projects/{name}/runs` - List runs filtered by project (new path-based approach)\n\n**JSON API Routes:**\n- `GET /api/runs` - List all runs as JSON (supports `?project=` query parameter)\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}` - Get run details as JSON\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` - Retrieve step output logs\n- `DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container` - Delete a retained container\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` - Server-sent events stream for live log viewing\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/runs` - List project-specific runs as JSON\n\n### Query Parameter Support\n\n**`/api/runs?project=<project-directory>`** (lines 497-522)\n- Filters runs by project directory path\n- If `project` query parameter is provided, filters to that project only\n- Otherwise returns all runs\n\n### Legacy URL Redirect\n\n**`GET /runs?project=<project-directory>`** (lines 250-259)\n- Old-style runs list with project filter query parameter\n- **Automatically redirects** (301 Moved Permanently) to: `/projects/<label>/runs`\n- Resolves project directory to its display label via `projectLabels()` function\n\n### Frontend/Template Links\n\n**In `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`:**\n- Inline links to individual runs: `<a href=\"/runs/{{.ID}}\">`\n- Project filter dropdown that triggers: `/projects/<label>/runs` (line 55)\n- JavaScript polling endpoints (lines 63-65):\n  - `/api/projects/<label>/runs` (when viewing project-specific runs)\n  - `/api/runs` (when viewing all runs)\n\n**In `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html`:**\n- Links to project-specific runs: `<a href=\"/projects/{{.Label}}/runs\">`\n- API trigger endpoint: `/api/projects/<label>/trigger`\n\n**In `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`:**\n- Links to all project runs: `<a href=\"/projects/{{.Label}}/runs\">`\n\n**In `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`:**\n- Links back to all runs: `<a href=\"/runs\">`\n- Live stream endpoint: `/api/runs/<run-id>/stream`\n- Step output endpoint: `/api/runs/<run-id>/steps/<step>/output`\n- Container deletion: DELETE `/api/runs/<run-id>/container`\n\n### Handler Functions\n\n| Function | Lines | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| `handleRunsList` | 250-298 | Render HTML list of all/filtered runs, handle legacy `?project=` redirects |\n| `handleProjectRunsList` | 300-344 | Render HTML list of runs for a specific project |\n| `handleRunDetail` | 426-453 | Render detailed run page with step execution history |\n| `handleAPIRuns` | 497-522 | JSON API returning all or project-filtered runs |\n| `handleAPIProjectRuns` | 524-546 | JSON API returning project-specific runs |\n| `handleAPIRunDetail` | 599-635 | JSON API with full run details including steps |\n| `handleAPIStepOutput` | 637-708 | Retrieve output logs for a specific step |\n| `handleAPIStream` | 790-849 | SSE stream for live log viewing |\n| `handleAPIDeleteContainer` | 710-746 | Delete a retained run container |\n\n### Test Coverage\n\nTests in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go` verify:\n- Lines 285-301: Legacy `?project=` redirect behavior (301 to `/projects/{label}/runs`)\n- Lines 316-343: API filtering via project-based URL paths\n\nAll relevant files are in the main workspace (not worktrees):\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Route definitions and handlers\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go` - Test cases\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Runs list template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Run detail template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` - Projects list template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Project detail template"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1467b5488ac5c2a3 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 63245\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 23927</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b51150cf-1c39-4197-a920-3b3045b4ca95","uuid":"6d8f4281-8de1-48fc-9cd9-6e2d4283ae42","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all files related to URL routing for \"runs\" endpoints, especially any that use \"runs?project=\" query parameter pattern or define routes/handlers for runs. Search for:\n1. Route definitions mentioning \"runs\"\n2. URLs with \"runs?project=\" \n3. Handler functions for runs endpoints\n4. Any frontend/template code that links to runs pages\n\nSearch broadly across the codebase.","agentId":"a1467b5488ac5c2a3","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my thorough search of the codebase, here's a comprehensive report of all URL routing for runs endpoints:\n\n## Summary of Runs Endpoint Routing\n\n### Route Definitions (in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - lines 139-162)\n\nThe main handler registers the following runs-related routes:\n\n**HTML Routes (Server-rendered pages):**\n- `GET /` - Project overview page\n- `GET /runs` - List all runs across all projects (handles legacy `?project=` redirects)\n- `GET /runs/{id}` - Run detail page for a specific run\n- `GET /projects/{name}` - Project detail page\n- `GET /projects/{name}/runs` - List runs filtered by project (new path-based approach)\n\n**JSON API Routes:**\n- `GET /api/runs` - List all runs as JSON (supports `?project=` query parameter)\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}` - Get run details as JSON\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` - Retrieve step output logs\n- `DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container` - Delete a retained container\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` - Server-sent events stream for live log viewing\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/runs` - List project-specific runs as JSON\n\n### Query Parameter Support\n\n**`/api/runs?project=<project-directory>`** (lines 497-522)\n- Filters runs by project directory path\n- If `project` query parameter is provided, filters to that project only\n- Otherwise returns all runs\n\n### Legacy URL Redirect\n\n**`GET /runs?project=<project-directory>`** (lines 250-259)\n- Old-style runs list with project filter query parameter\n- **Automatically redirects** (301 Moved Permanently) to: `/projects/<label>/runs`\n- Resolves project directory to its display label via `projectLabels()` function\n\n### Frontend/Template Links\n\n**In `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`:**\n- Inline links to individual runs: `<a href=\"/runs/{{.ID}}\">`\n- Project filter dropdown that triggers: `/projects/<label>/runs` (line 55)\n- JavaScript polling endpoints (lines 63-65):\n  - `/api/projects/<label>/runs` (when viewing project-specific runs)\n  - `/api/runs` (when viewing all runs)\n\n**In `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html`:**\n- Links to project-specific runs: `<a href=\"/projects/{{.Label}}/runs\">`\n- API trigger endpoint: `/api/projects/<label>/trigger`\n\n**In `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`:**\n- Links to all project runs: `<a href=\"/projects/{{.Label}}/runs\">`\n\n**In `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`:**\n- Links back to all runs: `<a href=\"/runs\">`\n- Live stream endpoint: `/api/runs/<run-id>/stream`\n- Step output endpoint: `/api/runs/<run-id>/steps/<step>/output`\n- Container deletion: DELETE `/api/runs/<run-id>/container`\n\n### Handler Functions\n\n| Function | Lines | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| `handleRunsList` | 250-298 | Render HTML list of all/filtered runs, handle legacy `?project=` redirects |\n| `handleProjectRunsList` | 300-344 | Render HTML list of runs for a specific project |\n| `handleRunDetail` | 426-453 | Render detailed run page with step execution history |\n| `handleAPIRuns` | 497-522 | JSON API returning all or project-filtered runs |\n| `handleAPIProjectRuns` | 524-546 | JSON API returning project-specific runs |\n| `handleAPIRunDetail` | 599-635 | JSON API with full run details including steps |\n| `handleAPIStepOutput` | 637-708 | Retrieve output logs for a specific step |\n| `handleAPIStream` | 790-849 | SSE stream for live log viewing |\n| `handleAPIDeleteContainer` | 710-746 | Delete a retained run container |\n\n### Test Coverage\n\nTests in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go` verify:\n- Lines 285-301: Legacy `?project=` redirect behavior (301 to `/projects/{label}/runs`)\n- Lines 316-343: API filtering via project-based URL paths\n\nAll relevant files are in the main workspace (not worktrees):\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Route definitions and handlers\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go` - Test cases\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Runs list template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Run detail template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` - Projects list template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Project detail template"}],"totalDurationMs":23927,"totalTokens":63245,"totalToolUseCount":18,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":168,"cache_read_input_tokens":61843,"output_tokens":1231,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{